42DOMCache::DOMCache(ScriptExecutionContext& context, String&& name, uint64_t identifier, Ref<CacheStorageConnection>&& connection)
43 : ActiveDOMObject(&context)
44 , m_name(WTFMove(name))
45 , m_identifier(identifier)
46 , m_connection(WTFMove(connection))
47{
48 suspendIfNeeded();
49 m_connection->reference(m_identifier);
50}
51
52DOMCache::~DOMCache()
53{
54 if (!m_isStopped)
55 m_connection->dereference(m_identifier);
56}

58void DOMCache::match(RequestInfo&& info, CacheQueryOptions&& options, Ref<DeferredPromise>&& promise)
59{
60 doMatch(WTFMove(info), WTFMove(options), [this, protectedThis = makeRef(*this), promise = WTFMove(promise)](ExceptionOr<RefPtr<FetchResponse>>&& result) mutable {
61 queueTaskKeepingObjectAlive(*this, TaskSource::DOMManipulation, [promise = WTFMove(promise), result = WTFMove(result)]() mutable {
62 if (result.hasException()) {
63 promise->reject(result.releaseException());
64 return;
65 }
66 if (!result.returnValue()) {
67 promise->resolve();
68 return;
69 }
70 promise->resolve<IDLInterface<FetchResponse>>(*result.returnValue());
71 });
72 });
73}
74
75static Ref<FetchResponse> createResponse(ScriptExecutionContext& context, const DOMCacheEngine::Record& record)
76{
77 auto resourceResponse = record.response;
78 resourceResponse.setSource(ResourceResponse::Source::DOMCache);
79 auto response = FetchResponse::create(context, std::nullopt, record.responseHeadersGuard, WTFMove(resourceResponse));
80 response->setBodyData(copyResponseBody(record.responseBody), record.responseBodySize);
81 return response;
82}
83
84void DOMCache::doMatch(RequestInfo&& info, CacheQueryOptions&& options, MatchCallback&& callback)
85{
86 if (UNLIKELY(!scriptExecutionContext()))
87 return;
88
89 auto requestOrException = requestFromInfo(WTFMove(info), options.ignoreMethod);
90 if (requestOrException.hasException()) {
91 callback(nullptr);
92 return;
93 }
94
95 auto request = requestOrException.releaseReturnValue()->resourceRequest();
96 queryCache(WTFMove(request), options, ShouldRetrieveResponses::Yes, [this, callback = WTFMove(callback)](auto&& result) mutable {
97 if (result.hasException()) {
98 callback(result.releaseException());
99 return;
100 }
101
102 RefPtr<FetchResponse> response;
103 if (!result.returnValue().isEmpty())
104 response = createResponse(*scriptExecutionContext(), result.returnValue()[0]);
105
106 callback(WTFMove(response));
107 });
108}
109
110Vector<Ref<FetchResponse>> DOMCache::cloneResponses(const Vector<DOMCacheEngine::Record>& records)
111{
112 return WTF::map(records, [this] (const auto& record) {
113 return createResponse(*scriptExecutionContext(), record);
114 });
115}

117void DOMCache::matchAll(std::optional<RequestInfo>&& info, CacheQueryOptions&& options, MatchAllPromise&& promise)
118{
119 if (UNLIKELY(!scriptExecutionContext()))
120 return;
121
122 ResourceRequest resourceRequest;
123 if (info) {
124 auto requestOrException = requestFromInfo(WTFMove(info.value()), options.ignoreMethod);
125 if (requestOrException.hasException()) {
126 promise.resolve({ });
127 return;
128 }
129 resourceRequest = requestOrException.releaseReturnValue()->resourceRequest();
130 }
131
132 queryCache(WTFMove(resourceRequest), options, ShouldRetrieveResponses::Yes, [this, promise = WTFMove(promise)](auto&& result) mutable {
133 queueTaskKeepingObjectAlive(*this, TaskSource::DOMManipulation, [this, promise = WTFMove(promise), result = WTFMove(result)]() mutable {
134 if (result.hasException()) {
135 promise.reject(result.releaseException());
136 return;
137 }
138 promise.resolve(cloneResponses(result.releaseReturnValue()));
139 });
140 });
141}
142
143void DOMCache::add(RequestInfo&& info, DOMPromiseDeferred<void>&& promise)
144{
145 addAll(Vector<RequestInfo> { WTFMove(info) }, WTFMove(promise));
146}
147
148static inline bool hasResponseVaryStarHeaderValue(const FetchResponse& response)
149{
150 auto varyValue = response.headers().internalHeaders().get(WebCore::HTTPHeaderName::Vary);
151 bool hasStar = false;
152 varyValue.split(',', [&](StringView view) {
153 if (!hasStar && stripLeadingAndTrailingHTTPSpaces(view) == "*")
154 hasStar = true;
155 });
156 return hasStar;
157}
158
159class FetchTasksHandler : public RefCounted<FetchTasksHandler> {
160public:
161 static Ref<FetchTasksHandler> create(Ref<DOMCache>&& domCache, CompletionHandler<void(ExceptionOr<Vector<Record>>&&)>&& callback) { return adoptRef(*new FetchTasksHandler(WTFMove(domCache), WTFMove(callback))); }
162
163 ~FetchTasksHandler()
164 {
165 if (m_callback)
166 m_callback(WTFMove(m_records));
167 }
168
169 const Vector<Record>& records() const { return m_records; }
170
171 size_t addRecord(Record&& record)
172 {
173 ASSERT(!isDone());
174 m_records.append(WTFMove(record));
175 return m_records.size() - 1;
176 }
177
178 void addResponseBody(size_t position, FetchResponse& response, DOMCacheEngine::ResponseBody&& data)
179 {
180 ASSERT(!isDone());
181 auto& record = m_records[position];
182 record.responseBodySize = m_domCache->connection().computeRecordBodySize(response, data);
183 record.responseBody = WTFMove(data);
184 }
185
186 bool isDone() const { return !m_callback; }
187
188 void error(Exception&& exception)
189 {
190 if (auto callback = WTFMove(m_callback))
191 callback(WTFMove(exception));
192 }
193
194private:
195 FetchTasksHandler(Ref<DOMCache>&& domCache, CompletionHandler<void(ExceptionOr<Vector<Record>>&&)>&& callback)
196 : m_domCache(WTFMove(domCache))
197 , m_callback(WTFMove(callback))
198 {
199 }
200
201 Ref<DOMCache> m_domCache;
202 Vector<Record> m_records;
203 CompletionHandler<void(ExceptionOr<Vector<Record>>&&)> m_callback;
204};
205
206ExceptionOr<Ref<FetchRequest>> DOMCache::requestFromInfo(RequestInfo&& info, bool ignoreMethod)
207{
208 RefPtr<FetchRequest> request;
209 if (WTF::holds_alternative<RefPtr<FetchRequest>>(info)) {
210 request = WTF::get<RefPtr<FetchRequest>>(info).releaseNonNull();
211 if (request->method() != "GET" && !ignoreMethod)
212 return Exception { TypeError, "Request method is not GET"_s };
213 } else
214 request = FetchRequest::create(*scriptExecutionContext(), WTFMove(info), { }).releaseReturnValue();
215
216 if (!request->url().protocolIsInHTTPFamily())
217 return Exception { TypeError, "Request url is not HTTP/HTTPS"_s };
218
219 return request.releaseNonNull();
220}
221
222void DOMCache::addAll(Vector<RequestInfo>&& infos, DOMPromiseDeferred<void>&& promise)
223{
224 if (UNLIKELY(!scriptExecutionContext()))
225 return;
226
227 Vector<Ref<FetchRequest>> requests;
228 requests.reserveInitialCapacity(infos.size());
229 for (auto& info : infos) {
230 bool ignoreMethod = false;
231 auto requestOrException = requestFromInfo(WTFMove(info), ignoreMethod);
232 if (requestOrException.hasException()) {
233 promise.reject(requestOrException.releaseException());
234 return;
235 }
236 requests.uncheckedAppend(requestOrException.releaseReturnValue());
237 }
238
239 auto taskHandler = FetchTasksHandler::create(*this, [this, protectedThis = makeRef(*this), promise = WTFMove(promise)](ExceptionOr<Vector<Record>>&& result) mutable {
240 if (result.hasException()) {
241 queueTaskKeepingObjectAlive(*this, TaskSource::DOMManipulation, [promise = WTFMove(promise), exception = result.releaseException()]() mutable {
242 promise.reject(WTFMove(exception));
243 });
244 return;
245 }
246 batchPutOperation(result.releaseReturnValue(), [this, protectedThis = WTFMove(protectedThis), promise = WTFMove(promise)](ExceptionOr<void>&& result) mutable {
247 queueTaskKeepingObjectAlive(*this, TaskSource::DOMManipulation, [promise = WTFMove(promise), result = WTFMove(result)]() mutable {
248 promise.settle(WTFMove(result));
249 });
250 });
251 });
252
253 for (auto& request : requests) {
254 auto& requestReference = request.get();
255 FetchResponse::fetch(*scriptExecutionContext(), requestReference, [this, request = WTFMove(request), taskHandler](ExceptionOr<FetchResponse&>&& result) mutable {
256
257 if (taskHandler->isDone())
258 return;
259
260 if (result.hasException()) {
261 taskHandler->error(result.releaseException());
262 return;
263 }
264
265 auto& response = result.releaseReturnValue();
266
267 if (!response.ok()) {
268 taskHandler->error(Exception { TypeError, "Response is not OK"_s });
269 return;
270 }
271
272 if (hasResponseVaryStarHeaderValue(response)) {
273 taskHandler->error(Exception { TypeError, "Response has a '*' Vary header value"_s });
274 return;
275 }
276
277 if (response.status() == 206) {
278 taskHandler->error(Exception { TypeError, "Response is a 206 partial"_s });
279 return;
280 }
281
282 CacheQueryOptions options;
283 for (const auto& record : taskHandler->records()) {
284 if (DOMCacheEngine::queryCacheMatch(request->resourceRequest(), record.request, record.response, options)) {
285 taskHandler->error(Exception { InvalidStateError, "addAll cannot store several matching requests"_s});
286 return;
287 }
288 }
289 size_t recordPosition = taskHandler->addRecord(toConnectionRecord(request.get(), response, nullptr));
290
291 response.consumeBodyReceivedByChunk([taskHandler = WTFMove(taskHandler), recordPosition, data = SharedBuffer::create(), response = makeRef(response)] (auto&& result) mutable {
292 if (taskHandler->isDone())
293 return;
294
295 if (result.hasException()) {
296 taskHandler->error(result.releaseException());
297 return;
298 }
299
300 if (auto* chunk = result.returnValue())
301 data->append(chunk->data(), chunk->size());
302 else
303 taskHandler->addResponseBody(recordPosition, response, WTFMove(data));
304 });
305 });
306 }
307}

309void DOMCache::putWithResponseData(DOMPromiseDeferred<void>&& promise, Ref<FetchRequest>&& request, Ref<FetchResponse>&& response, ExceptionOr<RefPtr<SharedBuffer>>&& responseBody)
310{
311 if (responseBody.hasException()) {
312 queueTaskKeepingObjectAlive(*this, TaskSource::DOMManipulation, [promise = WTFMove(promise), exception = responseBody.releaseException()]() mutable {
313 promise.reject(WTFMove(exception));
314 });
315 return;
316 }
317
318 DOMCacheEngine::ResponseBody body;
319 if (auto buffer = responseBody.releaseReturnValue())
320 body = buffer.releaseNonNull();
321 batchPutOperation(request.get(), response.get(), WTFMove(body), [this, protectedThis = makeRef(*this), promise = WTFMove(promise)](ExceptionOr<void>&& result) mutable {
322 queueTaskKeepingObjectAlive(*this, TaskSource::DOMManipulation, [promise = WTFMove(promise), result = WTFMove(result)]() mutable {
323 promise.settle(WTFMove(result));
324 });
325 });
326}
327
328void DOMCache::put(RequestInfo&& info, Ref<FetchResponse>&& response, DOMPromiseDeferred<void>&& promise)
329{
330 if (UNLIKELY(!scriptExecutionContext()))
331 return;
332
333 bool ignoreMethod = false;
334 auto requestOrException = requestFromInfo(WTFMove(info), ignoreMethod);
335 if (requestOrException.hasException()) {
336 promise.reject(requestOrException.releaseException());
337 return;
338 }
339 auto request = requestOrException.releaseReturnValue();
340
341 if (auto exception = response->loadingException()) {
342 promise.reject(*exception);
343 return;
344 }
345
346 if (hasResponseVaryStarHeaderValue(response.get())) {
347 promise.reject(Exception { TypeError, "Response has a '*' Vary header value"_s });
348 return;
349 }
350
351 if (response->status() == 206) {
352 promise.reject(Exception { TypeError, "Response is a 206 partial"_s });
353 return;
354 }
355
356 if (response->isDisturbedOrLocked()) {
357 promise.reject(Exception { TypeError, "Response is disturbed or locked"_s });
358 return;
359 }
360
361 if (response->isBlobFormData()) {
362 promise.reject(Exception { NotSupportedError, "Not implemented"_s });
363 return;
364 }
365
366 // FIXME: for efficiency, we should load blobs directly instead of going through the readableStream path.
367 if (response->isBlobBody()) {
368 auto streamOrException = response->readableStream(*scriptExecutionContext()->globalObject());
369 if (UNLIKELY(streamOrException.hasException())) {
370 promise.reject(streamOrException.releaseException());
371 return;
372 }
373 }
374
375 if (response->isBodyReceivedByChunk()) {
376 auto& responseRef = response.get();
377 responseRef.consumeBodyReceivedByChunk([promise = WTFMove(promise), request = WTFMove(request), response = WTFMove(response), data = SharedBuffer::create(), pendingActivity = makePendingActivity(*this), this](auto&& result) mutable {
378
379 if (result.hasException()) {
380 this->putWithResponseData(WTFMove(promise), WTFMove(request), WTFMove(response), result.releaseException().isolatedCopy());
381 return;
382 }
383
384 if (auto* chunk = result.returnValue())
385 data->append(chunk->data(), chunk->size());
386 else
387 this->putWithResponseData(WTFMove(promise), WTFMove(request), WTFMove(response), RefPtr<SharedBuffer> { WTFMove(data) });
388 });
389 return;
390 }
391
392 batchPutOperation(request.get(), response.get(), response->consumeBody(), [this, protectedThis = makeRef(*this), promise = WTFMove(promise)](ExceptionOr<void>&& result) mutable {
393 queueTaskKeepingObjectAlive(*this, TaskSource::DOMManipulation, [promise = WTFMove(promise), result = WTFMove(result)]() mutable {
394 promise.settle(WTFMove(result));
395 });
396 });
397}

399void DOMCache::remove(RequestInfo&& info, CacheQueryOptions&& options, DOMPromiseDeferred<IDLBoolean>&& promise)
400{
401 if (UNLIKELY(!scriptExecutionContext()))
402 return;
403
404 auto requestOrException = requestFromInfo(WTFMove(info), options.ignoreMethod);
405 if (requestOrException.hasException()) {
406 promise.resolve(false);
407 return;
408 }
409
410 batchDeleteOperation(requestOrException.releaseReturnValue(), WTFMove(options), [this, protectedThis = makeRef(*this), promise = WTFMove(promise)](ExceptionOr<bool>&& result) mutable {
411 queueTaskKeepingObjectAlive(*this, TaskSource::DOMManipulation, [promise = WTFMove(promise), result = WTFMove(result)]() mutable {
412 promise.settle(WTFMove(result));
413 });
414 });
415}

417static Ref<FetchRequest> createRequest(ScriptExecutionContext& context, const DOMCacheEngine::Record& record)
418{
419 auto requestHeaders = FetchHeaders::create(record.requestHeadersGuard, HTTPHeaderMap { record.request.httpHeaderFields() });
420 return FetchRequest::create(context, std::nullopt, WTFMove(requestHeaders), ResourceRequest { record.request }, FetchOptions { record.options }, String { record.referrer });
421}

423void DOMCache::keys(std::optional<RequestInfo>&& info, CacheQueryOptions&& options, KeysPromise&& promise)
424{
425 if (UNLIKELY(!scriptExecutionContext()))
426 return;
427
428 ResourceRequest resourceRequest;
429 if (info) {
430 auto requestOrException = requestFromInfo(WTFMove(info.value()), options.ignoreMethod);
431 if (requestOrException.hasException()) {
432 promise.resolve(Vector<Ref<FetchRequest>> { });
433 return;
434 }
435 resourceRequest = requestOrException.releaseReturnValue()->resourceRequest();
436 }
437
438 queryCache(WTFMove(resourceRequest), options, ShouldRetrieveResponses::No, [this, promise = WTFMove(promise)](auto&& result) mutable {
439 queueTaskKeepingObjectAlive(*this, TaskSource::DOMManipulation, [this, promise = WTFMove(promise), result = WTFMove(result)]() mutable {
440 if (result.hasException()) {
441 promise.reject(result.releaseException());
442 return;
443 }
444
445 auto records = result.releaseReturnValue();
446 promise.resolve(WTF::map(records, [this](auto& record) {
447 return createRequest(*scriptExecutionContext(), record);
448 }));
449 });
450 });
451}

453void DOMCache::queryCache(ResourceRequest&& request, const CacheQueryOptions& options, ShouldRetrieveResponses shouldRetrieveResponses, RecordsCallback&& callback)
454{
455 RetrieveRecordsOptions retrieveOptions { WTFMove(request), options.ignoreSearch, options.ignoreMethod, options.ignoreVary, shouldRetrieveResponses == ShouldRetrieveResponses::Yes };
456 m_connection->retrieveRecords(m_identifier, retrieveOptions, [this, pendingActivity = makePendingActivity(*this), callback = WTFMove(callback)](auto&& result) mutable {
457 if (m_isStopped) {
458 callback(DOMCacheEngine::convertToExceptionAndLog(scriptExecutionContext(), DOMCacheEngine::Error::Stopped));
459 return;
460 }
461
462 if (!result.has_value()) {
463 callback(DOMCacheEngine::convertToExceptionAndLog(scriptExecutionContext(), result.error()));
464 return;
465 }
466
467 callback(WTFMove(result.value()));
468 });
469
470}
471
472void DOMCache::batchDeleteOperation(const FetchRequest& request, CacheQueryOptions&& options, CompletionHandler<void(ExceptionOr<bool>&&)>&& callback)
473{
474 m_connection->batchDeleteOperation(m_identifier, request.internalRequest(), WTFMove(options), [this, pendingActivity = makePendingActivity(*this), callback = WTFMove(callback)](RecordIdentifiersOrError&& result) mutable {
475 if (m_isStopped) {
476 callback(DOMCacheEngine::convertToExceptionAndLog(scriptExecutionContext(), DOMCacheEngine::Error::Stopped));
477 return;
478 }
479
480 if (!result.has_value()) {
481 callback(DOMCacheEngine::convertToExceptionAndLog(scriptExecutionContext(), result.error()));
482 return;
483 }
484 callback(!result.value().isEmpty());
485 });
486}
487
488Record DOMCache::toConnectionRecord(const FetchRequest& request, FetchResponse& response, DOMCacheEngine::ResponseBody&& responseBody)
489{
490 auto cachedResponse = response.resourceResponse();
491 ResourceRequest cachedRequest = request.internalRequest();
492 cachedRequest.setHTTPHeaderFields(request.headers().internalHeaders());
493
494 ASSERT(!cachedRequest.isNull());
495 ASSERT(!cachedResponse.isNull());
496
497 auto sizeWithPadding = response.bodySizeWithPadding();
498 if (!sizeWithPadding) {
499 sizeWithPadding = m_connection->computeRecordBodySize(response, responseBody);
500 response.setBodySizeWithPadding(sizeWithPadding);
501 }
502
503 return { 0, 0,
504 request.headers().guard(), WTFMove(cachedRequest), request.fetchOptions(), request.internalRequestReferrer(),
505 response.headers().guard(), WTFMove(cachedResponse), WTFMove(responseBody), sizeWithPadding
506 };
507}
508
509void DOMCache::batchPutOperation(const FetchRequest& request, FetchResponse& response, DOMCacheEngine::ResponseBody&& responseBody, CompletionHandler<void(ExceptionOr<void>&&)>&& callback)
510{
511 Vector<Record> records;
512 records.append(toConnectionRecord(request, response, WTFMove(responseBody)));
513
514 batchPutOperation(WTFMove(records), WTFMove(callback));
515}
516
517void DOMCache::batchPutOperation(Vector<Record>&& records, CompletionHandler<void(ExceptionOr<void>&&)>&& callback)
518{
519 m_connection->batchPutOperation(m_identifier, WTFMove(records), [this, pendingActivity = makePendingActivity(*this), callback = WTFMove(callback)](auto&& result) mutable {
520 if (m_isStopped) {
521 callback(DOMCacheEngine::convertToExceptionAndLog(scriptExecutionContext(), DOMCacheEngine::Error::Stopped));
522 return;
523 }
524
525 if (!result.has_value()) {
526 callback(DOMCacheEngine::convertToExceptionAndLog(scriptExecutionContext(), result.error()));
527 return;
528 }
529 callback({ });
530 });
531}
532
533void DOMCache::stop()
534{
535 if (m_isStopped)
536 return;
537 m_isStopped = true;
538 m_connection->dereference(m_identifier);
539}

541const char* DOMCache::activeDOMObjectName() const
542{
543 return "Cache";
544}
